,doggystyle sex,bacon", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingCount": 317364, "bestRating": "10.0", "worstRating": "1.0", "ratingValue": "8.4"}, "review": {"@type": "Review", "itemReviewed": {"@type": "CreativeWork", "url": "/title/tt0087843/"}, "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "ccthemovieman-1"}, "dateCreated": "2005-11-26", "inLanguage": "English", "name": "Leone's \"Godfather\" Version, And About As Good", "reviewBody": "This Godfather-type film was done by Sergio Leone, of spaghetti-western fame, so you know you will see and experience several of his trademarks. Namely: (1) a lot of facial closeups; (2) some slow-motion or slow-moving dramatic scenes; (3) good overall photography and (4) a unique soundtrack.\n\nThe period sets here are magnificent. You get a real feel of the time, whether it's 1910, 1933 or 1967. The colors are awash in blacks, browns and grays and the DVD brings all these out very well, especially considering the film is over 20 years old.\n\nDespite some of Leone's slow moments, this is a fascinating film to watch for the story, too. There are numerous memorable scenes, some of them involving some downright shocking violence, even for today's movies. However, the amount of violence is less than what you see today.\n\nThe movie also sports an interesting twist near the end involving the two major characters, played by Robert De Niro and James Woods. The story is not always clear, either, so be prepared to be possibly confused about a few things....at least on the first viewing. Confused or not, this film always is fascinating to view, especially with intense actors such as the two men just mentioned, along with Elizabeth McGovern, Tuesday Weld, Joe Pecsi, Burt Young, Treat Williams and more.\n\nThe child actors in here take up almost half the movie and are excellent. What an injustice they don't receive any publicity for their acting, especially the kids who played De Niro and Woods as youngsters. One of the girls has become a famous adult actress: Jennifer Connelly. She was 12 years old in this film and was already alluring.\n\nThis is Godfather-type crime movie that ranks right up there with that famous film, not taking a back seat to it at all.", "reviewRating": {"@type": "Rating", "worstRating": "1", "bestRating": "10", "ratingValue": "8"}}, "duration": "PT3H49M", "trailer": {"@type": "VideoObject", "name": "Once Upon a Time in America", "embedUrl": "/video/imdb/vi2777395225", "thumbnail": {"@type": "ImageObject", "contentUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2FkYzkxNDctNTFhZi00M2Y2LTg1MzUtYTFlMTU2NzVmMmJlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg"}, "thumbnailUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2FkYzkxNDctNTFhZi00M2Y2LTg1MzUtYTFlMTU2NzVmMmJlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg", "description": "Trailer 2 for Once Upon A Time In America", "uploadDate": "2015-05-13T04:49:15Z"}, "cast_and_character": [{"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000134/?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Robert De Niro"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0087843/characters/nm0000134?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Noodles"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001527/?ref_=tt_cl_t3", "name": "Elizabeth McGovern"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0087843/characters/nm0001527?ref_=tt_cl_t3", "name": "Deborah"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001839/?ref_=tt_cl_t5", "name": "Tuesday Weld"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0087843/characters/nm0001839?ref_=tt_cl_t5", "name": "Carol"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000582/?ref_=tt_cl_t7", "name": "Joe Pesci"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0087843/characters/nm0000582?ref_=tt_cl_t7", "name": "Frankie"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001235/?ref_=tt_cl_t9", "name": "William Forsythe"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0087843/characters/nm0001235?ref_=tt_cl_t9", "name": "Cockeye"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url":